---

<Layout
  title="Century City High-End & Luxury Appliance Repair | (424) 499-7788"
  description="Luxury appliance repair in Century City for Sub-Zero, Wolf, Miele, Thermador, Gaggenau and other premium brands. Same-day or next-day service."
  structuredData={structuredData}
  ogImage="/high-end-and-luxury-appliance-repair-by-zaricci.webp"
>
  <ParallaxHeader client:idle />

  <div class="maincontent" id="webpage">
    <h2>Luxury Appliance Repair in Century City, Los Angeles</h2>

    <p>
      In Century City, appliance repair is often performed inside luxury
      condominium residences, high-rise apartments, mixed-use buildings, and
      carefully renovated units with premium built-in kitchens. Residences near
      Avenue of the Stars, Century Park East, Century Park West, Constellation
      Boulevard, Santa Monica Boulevard, and Olympic Boulevard frequently
      include integrated refrigerators, panel-ready dishwashers, wall ovens,
      induction cooktops, wine coolers, beverage centers, and stacked laundry
      systems that require precise diagnostics and careful workmanship.
    </p>

    <p>
      Century City service appointments can be different from repairs in
      detached homes. Building entry procedures, elevators, loading access,
      security desks, scheduled service windows, and compact built-in
      installations may all require additional care and planning. We work
      carefully around custom cabinetry, stone surfaces, finished flooring,
      and the surrounding areas of your home.
    </p>
  </div>

  <Tabs client:visible />

  <div class="maincontent" id="service">
    <section>
      <h3>Why Century City Residents Rely on ZARICCI</h3>

      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>✅ Experienced with Integrated Luxury Appliances</strong>
          <br />
          We service premium built-in and panel-ready appliances, including
          Sub-Zero refrigerators, Wolf cooking appliances, Miele dishwashers
          and laundry systems, Thermador appliances, Gaggenau appliances,
          and other luxury brands commonly installed in high-end residences.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>✅ Careful Service for Condos and High-Rise Residences</strong>
          <br />
          We understand that appliance service inside a condominium or
          high-rise residence requires attention to building procedures,
          elevator access, finished flooring, cabinetry, neighbors, and
          shared residential spaces.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>✅ Built-In Kitchen Diagnostic Experience</strong>
          <br />
          Integrated appliances may require a more careful diagnostic
          approach because ventilation, cabinet clearances, panel alignment,
          electrical access, water connections, and installation conditions
          can affect performance.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>✅ OEM Parts Whenever Available</strong>
          <br />
          Your appliances are an investment. When replacement components are
          needed, we identify the appropriate OEM, manufacturer-approved, or
          compatible part for the specific appliance and model.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>✅ Same-Day or Next-Day Scheduling</strong>
          <br />
          We offer priority scheduling in Century City whenever appointment
          availability and building access allow, with respect for your time,
          privacy, and home.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>✅ Discreet, White-Glove Repair Experience</strong>
          <br />
          We maintain a clean workspace, communicate clearly, and provide the
          professional service expected in a carefully maintained residence.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Our Luxury Repair Process</h3>

      <ol>
        <li>
          <strong>Book Your Appointment</strong>
          <br />
          Call or schedule online. We will confirm your preferred time and
          gather basic information about your appliance, residence, and any
          building-access requirements.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Arrival & Building Access</strong>
          <br />
          Your ZARICCI technician arrives for the scheduled appointment and
          follows the appropriate entry, parking, elevator, and service-access
          procedures for the property.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Brand-Specific Diagnosis</strong>
          <br />
          We inspect the appliance carefully and use the diagnostic approach
          appropriate for the appliance type, symptoms, installation, and
          surrounding cabinetry.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Clear, Upfront Estimate</strong>
          <br />
          We explain the issue and provide a transparent quote before
          proceeding with the recommended repair.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Precision Repair & Performance Testing</strong>
          <br />
          We complete the approved repair, restore appliance function, and
          test the relevant systems for proper performance.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong>Final Walkthrough & Service Warranty</strong>
          <br />
          We clean the work area, answer your questions, and explain the
          warranty that applies to the completed service.
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Serving Century City Condos, Apartments & High-Rise Residences</h3>

      <p>
        We serve Century City residences near Avenue of the Stars, Century
        Park East, Century Park West, Constellation Boulevard, Santa Monica
        Boulevard, Olympic Boulevard, and Pico Boulevard. Our service is
        designed for condominium residences, apartments, mixed-use buildings,
        and carefully renovated homes where clean workmanship, discretion,
        and precise diagnostics matter.
      </p>

      <p>
        Century City kitchens often rely on integrated refrigeration,
        panel-ready dishwashers, built-in wall ovens, induction cooktops,
        compact laundry systems, wine coolers, ice makers, and undercounter
        beverage centers. These appliances may be concealed behind custom
        panels or installed within cabinetry with limited access, making a
        careful repair approach especially important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Careful Service for Built-In and Panel-Ready Appliances</h3>

      <p>
        Built-in luxury appliances require more than a quick visual inspection.
        A cooling issue may involve ventilation, airflow, temperature sensors,
        condenser access, door alignment, or installation conditions. A
        dishwasher leak may require careful inspection around custom panels,
        flooring, and cabinetry. A wall oven or cooktop issue may involve
        electrical access, control systems, ventilation, or precise cabinet
        integration.
      </p>

      <p>
        At <strong>ZARICCI</strong>, we approach each appliance with attention
        to its installation, surrounding finishes, and the practical needs of
        the residence.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>Your Home Deserves More Than a Quick Fix</h3>

      <p>
        Your luxury appliances were selected for their performance,
        craftsmanship, and design. At <strong>ZARICCI</strong>, we deliver a
        repair experience that reflects those same values—with skill,
        discretion, and careful service from start to finish.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h3>📞 Schedule Your Luxury Appliance Repair in Century City Today</h3>

      <p>
        Do not wait for a small appliance issue to become a major disruption.
        <br />
        Call <strong>Luxury Appliance Repair by Zaricci</strong> or book online
        now to schedule expert service in Century City, Los Angeles.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>
          ZARICCI — Because Century City Homes Deserve World-Class Repair.
        </strong>
      </p>
    </section>

    <Logos client:visible />
    <Reviews client:idle />
  </div>
</Layout>